holidays.name: Makar Sankranti
holidays.description: Harvest festival celebrated across India, marking the transition of the sun into the zodiac sign Capricorn.

holidays.name: Republic Day
holidays.description: Commemorates the adoption of the Indian Constitution on January 26, 1950.

holidays.name: Holi
holidays.description: Festival of colors celebrating the arrival of spring and the victory of good over evil.

holidays.name: Mahavir Jayanti
holidays.description: Celebrates the birth of Lord Mahavir, the 24th Tirthankara of Jainism.

holidays.name: Baisakhi
holidays.description: Harvest festival celebrated in Punjab, marking the Punjabi New Year.

holidays.name: Eid al-Fitr
holidays.description: Marks the end of Ramadan, the Islamic holy month of fasting.

holidays.name: Independence Day
holidays.description: Celebrates India's independence from British rule on August 15, 1947.

holidays.name: Navratri
holidays.description: Nine-night festival celebrating the goddess Durga in her various forms.

holidays.name: Gandhi Jayanti
holidays.description: Honors the birth anniversary of Mahatma Gandhi.

holidays.name: Diwali
holidays.description: Festival of Lights celebrated across India.

holidays.name: Guru Nanak Jayanti
holidays.description: Celebrates the birth of Guru Nanak, the founder of Sikhism.

holidays.name: Christmas
holidays.description: Celebration of the birth of Jesus Christ.
